2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper proposes user scheduling algorithms for a cellular network, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses power allocation and mode switching in a cellular network, which can be viewed as control problems. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper analyzes the system rate performance of the proposed algorithms, which can be related to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society): This category is less likely, but the paper may have implications for the societal impact of full-duplex cellular networks, such as their potential to improve wireless communication efficiency and capacity.
